ZCZC EE04
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 172300 UTC
A LARGE COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE LIES SITUATED OVER THE EERN ATLANTIC
TO THE SW OF ICELAND THURSDAY EVENING 985 AND DRIFTS SLWY N AND E WHILST
FLN THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD. THIS IS EXP TO PUSH FRONTAL SYSTEMS N AND EWARDS
ACROSS THE UK DURING THE LATTER PART OF THE WEEK. MEANWHILE THE AZORES HIGH
LOOKS TO LOOKS TO BUILD A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE ACROSS FITZROY FORMING
A HIGH PRESSURE AROUND 1020 ACROSS THE ENGLISH CHANNEL THROUGH THOUGH MUCH
OF THE PERIOD. THIS HIGH DOES RECLINING BACK S-WWARDS INTO FRIDAY FOR A TIME
AS A SHORT LIVED SHALLOW LOW MOVS UP FM THE NEAR CONTINENT. STRG WINDS LIKELY
SHANNON AND POSSIBLY FASTNET THROUGH THURSDAY GENERALLY EASING BUT OCCASIONAL
STRG WINDS PERSISTING FOR SHANNON THROUGH THE PERIOD. SOME OCCASIONAL STRG
WINDS ARE ALSO POSS FOR SERN PARTS OF FITZROY THROUGH FRIDAY AND SATURDAY
